      "content": "The idea of infrastructure acting as an energetic \"mechanism\" is a concept found in various schools of thought, blending architecture with metaphysics, but direct, scientific evidence for encoded energy flows in city grids is lacking. However, the prominence of financial and governmental centers within grand, geometric urban plans is a consistent pattern seen globally. Many historic capital cities were deliberately designed to manifest the values of their ruling institutions through monumental and ordered architecture.",
